Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of end-to-end neural text-to-speech (TTS) methods using the Transformer network, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. 
2. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper deals with generating audio results using a WaveNet vocoder, which is a type of generative model for audio synthesis. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper involves processing of audio signals to generate speech, which falls under the domain of signal processing. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new neural network architecture for TTS using the Transformer network, which is a type of deep learning model. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves designing a system for generating speech from text using neural networks, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
